11/08/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Dervis Eroglu held another round of talks Tuesday (August 10th) aimed at reunifying the divided island. They focused this time on the property issue. UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon's special adviser on Cyprus, Alexander Downer, described the discussions as "good" and said they will resume at the end of the month after a short summer break. (UN News Centre, CNA - 10/08/10)
